blurb: Java is a very widely used Object Oriented programming language. It's safe, simple to use and portable so that you can "write once, run anywhere".

key_features.title: Modern
key_features.content: Java is a modern, fast-evolving language with releases every 6 months.

key_features.title: Statically-typed
key_features.content: Every expression has a type known at compile time.

key_features.title: Multi-paradigm
key_features.content: Java is primarily an object-oriented language, but has many functional features introduced in v1.8.

key_features.title: General purpose
key_features.content: Java is used for a variety of workloads like web, cloud, mobile and game applications.

key_features.title: Portable
key_features.content: Java was designed to be cross-platform with the slogan "Write once, run anywhere".

key_features.title: Garbage Collection
key_features.content: Java programs perform automatic memory management for their lifecycles.
